3:15 p.m. Elizabeth Gebert appears for State of Wisconsin. Attorney Cana Kohn appears for Defendant Janet N. Bailey. Janet N. Bailey appears, in custody. 16CF32, 18CF158, 18CF213 called. State has received revocation summary, no corrections or additions. Agreement stated  Def will plead to 18CF213 cts 1 & 2, 18CF158 dri. 18CF213 on each ct 6 yrs prison, 3 yrs ic, 3 yrs es, concurrent to each other and to any other. Credit for 16 days.  16CF32 join DOC recommendation 1 yr ic, 1 yr es, concurrent to any. Credit for 333 days served. Atty Kohn and Def agree. No corrections or additions to rev summary. Court reviews prelim hrg rights w/Def. Finds waiver knowing and voluntary, finds probable cause and binds over. State is filing information electronically. Atty Kohn willing to proceed as long as information mirrors complaint. Plea quest. reviewed. Plea to 18CF213 ct 1  guilty, ct 2  guilty. Court grants motion to dismiss and read in 18CF158 both counts. Constitutional rights, elements, possible penalties reviewed. Atty Kohn satisfied. Court finds Def understands and pleas freely and voluntarily made. Factual basis. Court accepts pleas and finds Def guilty of 18CF213 cts 1 & 2. Sentencing remarks by the State. Sentencing remarks by Atty Kohn. Statement by Defendant. Remarks by the Court. Will follow recommendation. 16CF32 ct 1-  2 yrs prison, 1 yr ic, 1 yr es, credit for 333 days. Any outstanding obligations to be paid through ext. supv. 18CF213 on each ct  6 yrs prison, 3 yrs ic, 3 yrs es, concurrent to each other and to any other sentence. Court costs and DNA surcharge on each, DNA sample if not already on file. Credit for 16 days served. Def eligible for SAP, not eligible for CIP. Def advised of firearms and voting restrictions. Postconviction rights.  Atty Kohn advises has reviewed information filed in 18CF213 and does mirror complaint.
